  <description><![CDATA[<p>Fancy something out of the ordinary? Inghams summer holidays in Germany let you explore the wonderful scenery and sights of Germany from an extremely comfortable base. The superb 5 star <a data-udi="umb://document/353e55dfe81747c585f91c0786463ea3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/353e55dfe81747c585f91c0786463ea3}" title="Steigenberger Inselhotel">Steigenberger Inselhotel</a> is perched on the shores of picturesque Lake Constance, part of the lakes in Germany. You might not expect to find palm trees and exotic greenery in Germany, but holidays in this part of Germany offer exactly that. The region's special microclimate is balmy and warm, delightful to wander around in on bright summer evenings. A summer holiday on Lake Constance also delivers fine food, wonderful service, excellent local wines, festivals and vibrant culture all year round. Plus there's an amazing array of outdoor and indoor activities making Lake Constance the ideal sight-seeing vacation.</p>
<p>Our walking holidays in Germany, in the farthest corner of south-east Germany, offer spectacular natural beauty including majestic mountains and crystal clear lakes. In this marvellous area of Bavaria, the wider areas of <a data-udi="umb://document/94bca848a3044053aa285430bda2bb78" href="/{localLink:umb://document/94bca848a3044053aa285430bda2bb78}" title="Ruhpolding">Ruhpolding</a> and the <a data-udi="umb://document/04e03f5c842c48279d8406095eb78480" href="/{localLink:umb://document/04e03f5c842c48279d8406095eb78480}" title="Berchtesgaden">Berchtesgadener Land </a>host many popular sites such as the Eagle’s Nest, historic salt mines as well as the enchanting Königssee. The countryside is unspoiled, with stunning landscapes and lake views that'll quite simply take your breath away. Alternatively, discover the best of Lake Constance with our Castles &amp; Gardens of Lake Constance escorted tour. Travelling in a small group with a knowledgeable guide throughout, you'll discover the regions most beautiful gardens and uncover the unique history of its many historic castles and palaces.</p>
<p>In Germany, holidays offer much more than sausages, beer and big cities! German summer holidays combine some of the best scenery into one relatively small area. Imagine sitting on a sun-warmed rock at <a data-udi="umb://document/352137bbbdf44ec4ac7857b5a613deb4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/352137bbbdf44ec4ac7857b5a613deb4}" title="Lake Constance">Lake Constance's</a> shore as the sun goes down, discovering the picturesque mountain village of <a data-udi="umb://document/94bca848a3044053aa285430bda2bb78" href="/{localLink:umb://document/94bca848a3044053aa285430bda2bb78}" title="Ruhpolding">Ruhpolding</a> and its many alluring meadows and gentle hills, by foot or bike. Exploring the busy little Bavarian town of <a data-udi="umb://document/04e03f5c842c48279d8406095eb78480" href="/{localLink:umb://document/04e03f5c842c48279d8406095eb78480}" title="Berchtesgaden">Berchtesgaden</a> in the mountains in Germany, taking advantage of loads of tiny, interesting shops in the old town of Meersburg, or boarding a lake steamer for a luxurious and delightfully scenic lake boat trip. All in all, we highly recommend our summer holidays, for some of Germany's most beautiful countryside. Book your perfect Germany holidays here!</p>]]></description>
